      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<div class=\"contentLayout2\"><style>[data-colorid=wvj811kwnb]{color:#3d90b3} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=wvj811kwnb]{color:#4c9fc2}</style>\n<div class=\"columnLayout fixed-width\" data-layout=\"fixed-width\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<p /><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"RenderMan_Solaris_SoloNodes.jpg\" width=\"1001\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544641013/RenderMan_Solaris_SoloNodes.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433084305&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1001&amp;height=539\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544641013/RenderMan_Solaris_SoloNodes.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433084305&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"1381\" data-width=\"2560\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544641025\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Solaris_SoloNodes.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544641013\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"d6711c4b-c872-4e15-9250-b0da905ef891\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544641013/RenderMan_Solaris_SoloNodes.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433084305&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=2002&amp;height=1078 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544641013/RenderMan_Solaris_SoloNodes.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433084305&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1001&amp;height=539 1x\" /></span><p><br />Artists can solo shading nodes and sections of material networks using the Visualizer node, to aid in lookdev and artistic control.&nbsp;<br /><br />This is especially useful when dialing in the look of a layer mask, adjusting a texture map, or getting those fingerprint grunge maps looking just right on toy ice cream trucks!</p><p>To solo a node or incoming shading network, simply select the node you wish to solo and press the <strong><span data-colorid=\"wvj811kwnb\">X</span></strong> key.&nbsp; <br />Doing so, will insert a visualize node and automatically connect the output of the selected node to the input of the <em>visualize </em>node.&nbsp; <br /><br />To 'un-solo' a node, cut the input to the <em>visualize </em>node and continue working on the lookdev.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><br /></p><hr /><p /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"columnLayout two-equal\" data-layout=\"two-equal\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-left-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-left\" width=\"839\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544641013/RenderMan_Solaris_SoloNodes_1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433084532&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=839&amp;height=451\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544641013/RenderMan_Solaris_SoloNodes_1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433084532&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"678\" data-width=\"1259\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544641037\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Solaris_SoloNodes_1.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544641013\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"07d8c70a-0212-4